## Part 1 — Branch protection rules

Configure these on every Application repo (or inherit via Application subgroup settings in GitLab):

| Branch | Protected | Allowed to push | Allowed to merge | Allow force push | Delete |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| `main` | Yes | No one | `epay-gitlab-bank-app-maintainer` + `epay-gitlab-bank-app-owner` | No | No |
| `develop` | Yes | No one | `epay-gitlab-vendor-app-lead` | No | No |
| `release/*` | Yes | No one | `epay-gitlab-vendor-app-maintainer` | No | No |
| `feature/*` | No | Developer+ | — | — | Auto-delete on merge |
| `bugfix/*` | No | Developer+ | — | — | Auto-delete on merge |
| `hotfix/*` | No | Developer+ | — | — | Auto-delete on merge |

> On `main` and `develop` — "No one" on push means even Owners can't push directly. All changes must go through an approved MR. Set this explicitly in GitLab's branch protection UI.

