## Part 2 — Push rules (Repository → Push Rules)

Set these at the Application subgroup level so they inherit across all repos:

| Rule | Value |
|---|---|
| Branch name regex | `^(main\|develop\|release\/[0-9]+\.[0-9]+\.[0-9]+\|feature\/EPAY-[0-9]+-[a-z0-9-]+\|bugfix\/EPAY-[0-9]+-[a-z0-9-]+\|hotfix\/[0-9]+\.[0-9]+\.[0-9]+)$` |
| Commit message regex | `^(feat\|fix\|docs\|style\|refactor\|perf\|test\|chore)\(.+\): .+ EPAY-[0-9]+$` |
| Reject unsigned commits | Based on your bank's compliance stance |
| Do not allow users to remove git tags | Yes |
| Reject commits that change files that should not be changed | Not applicable here |
| Check whether commit author is a GitLab user | Yes |

> The branch name regex will reject any push to a branch that doesn't match the naming convention — preventing ad-hoc branches like `fix-bug` or `om-test`.

